value.title: Pence seeks dismissal of suit aiming to overturn election
value.excerpt: The Justice Department has asked a federal judge to dismiss a last-gasp lawsuit led by a House Republican that seeks to give Vice President Mike Pence the power to overturn the results of the presiden

value.title: What Will Pence Do When Congress Counts the Votes?
value.excerpt: Readers are shocked that the question is being asked and speculate that the vice president may find an excuse not to be present. They also criticize Senator Josh Hawley.

value.title: Mike Pence heading to Georgia on Monday ahead of runoff elections
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence is heading to Georgia on Monday to campaign ahead of Tuesday’s critical U.S. Senate runoff elections.

value.title: With Trump a no-show, Mar-a-Lago guests left to party maskless with Rudy Giuliani and Vanilla Ice
value.excerpt: Guests who paid four-figures for tickets to President Donald Trump's annual New Year's Eve party were left to party with his personal attorney Rudy Giuliani, his two adult sons and various figures from the conservative media — none of whom wore masks — after the President made a last-minute decision

value.title: Fact check: President Trump spent Thanksgiving with troops in Afghanistan in 2019, not 2020
value.excerpt: Social media users having been sharing posts that claim President Donald Trump spent Thanksgiving 2020 with troops in Bagram, Afghanistan, not playing golf. This claim is false: the photo of Trump in Bagram is from 2019.

value.title: Trump attacks and vote by mail: the top voting rights stories of 2020
value.excerpt: The pandemic created new barriers to the ballot box and strengthened existing ones – aided by the president and his Republican allies

value.title: GOP senator rebukes 'dangerous ploy' to fight Biden victory
value.excerpt: Republican Sen. Ben Sasse of Nebraska has issued a pointed rebuke of GOP attempts to object Jan. 6 to the Electoral College tally of the presidential election, warning colleagues against a “dangerous ploy” that could damage the nation's civic traditions.

value.title: Trump reflects on his 'historic victories' in new year message
value.excerpt: Biden looks ahead to 2021 in upbeat message as Trump points out he correctly predicted arrival of vaccine before year’s end

value.title: From covfefe to the Mooch: 10 funny moments from the Trump presidency
value.excerpt: Amid four years of corruption, caging children and trashing democracy there were some light-hearted moments – no really

value.title: Trump reportedly lashed out at Kushner over increased COVID-19 testing: 'I'm going to lose, and it's going to be your fault'
value.excerpt: Trump reportedly told Kushner, "I want to do what Mexico does. They don't give you a test till you get to the emergency room and you're vomiting."

value.title: Trump extends visa ban, health coverage policy advances
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump has extended pandemic-related bans on green cards and work visas to large groups of applicants through March 31

value.title: Amid election turmoil caused by Trump, Chief Justice Roberts lauds judiciary for pandemic response
value.excerpt: Roberts notably avoided any mention of the judiciary's other historic challenges caused in large part by President Donald Trump, his frequent nemesis.

value.title: One of Trump's 'biggest services to America' was exposing liberal media: Jeffrey Lord
value.excerpt: One of President Trump's top accomplishments came not on the domestic policy or foreign policy front, but in simply exposing left-wing media figures for their biases, columnist and political analyst Jeffrey Lord said Wednesday on "The Ingraham Angle."

value.title: Biden inauguration events to include memorial for COVID-19 victims
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden plans a lighting ceremony at the Lincoln Memorial Reflecting Pool to honor COVID-19 victims the day before his swearing-in.

value.title: Computer repairman: Twitter calling me hacker in Hunter Biden laptop case was 'death sentence'
value.excerpt: The computer repairman at the center of the Hunter Biden laptop story said Thursday that Twitter destroyed his business by labeling him a "hacker" and legal action was his only recourse.

value.title: Biden's inaugural committee hosting national memorial for Covid-19 victims on January 19
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden's inaugural committee on Thursday announced that it is hosting a national memorial to remember and honor the lives lost to Covid-19 and is asking cities and towns around the country to participate.

value.title: Trump versus the truth: The most outrageous falsehoods of his presidency
value.excerpt: I have never seen a president in American history who has lied so continuously and so outrageously as Donald Trump, period,” presidential historian Michael Beschloss said.

value.title: Alec Baldwin should play himself in 'SNL' sketch about wife's heritage controversy: Trump Jr.
value.excerpt: Donald Trump Jr Wednesday suggested actor Alec Baldwin should play himself in a "Saturday Night Live" sketch about his wife Hilaria’s scandal over her heritage.

value.title: Trump makes 2nd request to Supreme Court over Wisconsin loss
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump on Wednesday asked the U.S. Supreme Court to overturn his election loss in Wisconsin, his second appeal in as many days to the high court over the result in the key battleground state.

value.title: Biden campaign promises included decriminalizing HIV exposure
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden has promised to "advance LGBTQ equality" by reversing decades-old criminalization of HIV exposure and transmission laws that have no "scientific basis" and contribute to stigmas.

value.title: Biden transition chief blasts ‘obstruction’ by political appointees at OMB, Pentagon
value.excerpt: Yohannes Abraham said a lack of cooperation was limiting the president-elect’s ability to mount an effective economic response to the pandemic.

value.title: Census Bureau to miss deadline, threatening Trump's attempt to exclude illegal migrants from census
value.excerpt: For the first time in four decades the Census Bureau will miss their deadline on reporting apportionment figures used to divvy up congressional seats.

value.title: Trump was briefed that China sought to pay non-state actors to attack US forces in Afghanistan
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump received information earlier this month that China sought to pay non-state actors to attack American forces in Afghanistan, a senior administration official said.

value.title: Acosta's admission he'll go easier on Biden shows 'personal vendetta' against Trump: Kurtz
value.excerpt: Fox News media analyst Howard Kurtz told "America’s Newsroom" Wednesday that CNN White House correspondent Jim Acosta’s admission he will approach a Biden White House in less adversarial fashion shows he's brought a "personal vendetta" to his reporting on the Trump administration.

value.title: Thomas L. Friedman column: Will Trump force principled conservatives to start their own party? I hope so.
value.excerpt: As the Trump presidency heads into the sunset, kicking and screaming, one of the most important questions that will shape American politics at the local, state and national levels is this: Can Donald Trump maintain his iron grip over the Republican Party when he is out of office?
